<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-4 Functions of Several Variables</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete all three parts. To earn a P on this outcome, 
      you will need to correctly complete part a, one of parts b or c with progress on the other.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
    <task><statement><p>Given the function <m>f(x,y)=\ln(9 - x^2 - y^2)</m>. State the domain of <m>f(x,y)</m> using correct set notation.</p></statement></task>
    <task><statement><p>Find the limit, if it exists, or prove that the limit does not exist. <md>\lim_{(x,y) \to (0,0)} \frac{2x^2y}{x^4+y^2}</md></p></statement></task>
    <task><statement><p>Find the limit, if it exists, or prove that the limit does not exist. <md>\lim_{(x,y,z) \to (2,1,0)} \frac{x^2y + \cos(\pi z)}{y+1}</md></p></statement></task>
  </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>